Hello Professor Vaserstein, =20

=20

I'm writing to you in your capacity as a Professor of Mathematics at
Penn State. There are Analyst opportunities at Capital One located in
Richmond, VA and Washington, DC that I want to make certain your
students are aware of. We would be grateful for your assistance in
passing this information along to your students who may be interested in
this position, which is described below.=20

=20

If students are interested in being considered for this position, please
have them apply through the Penn State Career Center's website
(nacelink.com) as soon as possible, as we will be starting the selection
process next week. However, should any of your students have any
questions, please have them contact Ginger Hassler at 312.867.2352 or
gh@on-campus.com <mailto:gh@on-campus.com> .

=20

Snapshot

As an Analyst at Capital One, you'll apply your strategic skills and
business instincts to major company challenges. You'll team with
world-class professionals to take projects from testing to
implementation. And you'll do it all in a collaborative environment that
values your insight, encourages you to take on new responsibility,
promotes continuous learning and rewards innovation.

=20

Capital One offers exceptional opportunities to develop your abilities
as an Analyst. You'll be part of a culture that emphasizes professional
development, integrity and work/life balance.

=20

=20

Typical responsibilities

Capital One highly values the role Analysts play in our success. That's
why Analysts work in all strategic areas of the company-such as
Marketing and Analysis, Operations and other areas.  Along with
team-based training, you'll receive mentoring and ad hoc partnering with
colleagues to help you quickly develop the practical knowledge you need
in new areas. As an Analyst, you could be involved in projects spanning
a wide spectrum of business functions and your responsibilities may
include:

=20

* Conducting research and performing basic analysis of demographics,
products and business lines

* Performing ad hoc analysis of business situations, issues and problems

* Conducting data query and competitive analysis, including NPV and ROI
assessments

* Developing computer-generated financial and statistical models

* Analyzing marketing channels and exploring new business opportunities

* Serving as an internal consultant focusing on re-engineering analysis

* Formulating actionable, value-adding business solutions and managing
project implementation for those strategies

=20

=20

General qualifications

* Degree in a quantitative major, including economics, finance,
engineering and operations research

* Strong standardized test scores (i.e. SAT, ACT, GMAT, GRE)

* Strong quantitative, analytical, problem solving and conceptual skills

* Strong interpersonal and leadership skills

* Ability to work in a fast-paced, collaborative environment

* Ability to handle multiple concurrent projects

=20

Thank you in advance for your time.=20

=20

=20

Best Regards,=20

=20

Anna Ming

=20


